From 0b476710a9a9618943302f64b43b3fa22cd01052 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shwetha G K <kshwetha@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 16:14:42 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Handle TTLM status update event

There are three types of events sent from the firmware after it
receives the TTLM configurations from userspace. First, the
Mapping Switch Time (MST) update: the mapping switch time provided
by the user for an MLD via the CLI command is in TU units. The
firmware converts this value into TSF units for each link in the
MLD and sends an event per link with the converted value. This
value must be stored per link and included in the TTLM IE. Second,
the MST expiry: when the MST expires, the firmware sends an
indication, after which the AP begins advertising the TTLM
configured by the user. Third, the Expected Duration (ED) expiry:
once the ED expires, the firmware sends an indication, and the AP
stops advertising the established TTLM and reverts to the default
mapping. This commit adds a handler for the MST update to ensure
the updated value is included in the beacon when operating in
non-beacon-offload mode. It also adds handlers for MST and ED
expiry events, invoking hostapd_ttlm_handle_mapping_switch_time_expiry()
to promote upcoming_ttlm to established_ttlm, and
hostapd_ttlm_handle_expected_duration_expiry() to clear the
established_ttlm.

Signed-off-by: Shwetha G K <kshwetha@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Amith A <amitajit@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
